DaVinci Pizzeria hit another "Grand-Slam Homerun" in my book !!  Unfortunately, due to the COVID-19 pandemic lockdown and NYC / state imposed quarantining restrictions, I was unable to return to my native hometown of Brooklyn, NY for the 2020 holiday season.  Instead, I brought the best of Brooklyn, NY home to Maryland.  I placed orders for both Sicilian and round pies from the FABULOUS DaVinci Pizzeria online, (in addition to Junior's Cheesecake + Katz's Delicatessen) and it's making me feel right at home, almost as though I never stepped out of Brooklyn.  DaVinci's Pizzeria deserves a perfect "Ten-Star" rating all the way !!  Hopefully, once this COVID-19 pandemic is under control, I'll be able to get back to my roots some time in 2021.

One of the best old-school pizza joints in Brooklyn, located in the heart of what used to be the Italian-American mecca of NYC. While the neighborhood around  it has transformed, this pizzeria has not.  The pizza itself is phenomenal - crispy crust and dough, just the right amount of cheese,and perfect sauce. I would come here everyday if my waistline wouldn't punish me for it.  I would, however, stick to just pizza. The calzone we ordered was a bit lacking, but that's the usual in pizzerias like this one.  Also, small note that I wish they would change - they don't deliver :(

The pizza is simply delicious. The plain slice has that sauce that's just right. Right amount of tangy and with the right blend of whatever it is that makes it taste like those rare pizzerias of New York of old. The crust is just right, not limp or soggy and not too overcooked. Really brings me back. The white ricotta slice is so creamy and rich. Not too oily or salty. You can tell that they really use quality ingredients. The well groomed man at the counter was very courteous and friendly. The decor is quaint and old school, but nothing to take your breath away. The main attraction here is the pizza and that's what the focus is on. You will not be dissappointed with the pizza. Even the customers are friendly. Some old Italian women come here and exchange kisses on the cheek with the man behind the counter. This is the real deal old school pizzeria that's been around since 1966.

Have been going to this place since i was a kid. Used to live down the block (many years ago lol) and it was always the best pizza in the neighborhood, and that's when there were many good pizzerias in the area (its different today). But DaVinci has withstood the test of time. They continue to make amazing pizza. Their crown jewel is their squares. Now that i moved to the other side of Brooklyn, i do not go as much, but when i want good pizza, will make the trip or send someone to get a few pies (always get an extra pie, you can freeze them and they taste amazing when you reheat them in the toaster oven nice and crispy).  Great friendly service in an old school spot. This time we got a plain Sicilian (square) and a Sicilian with 1/2 sausage / 1/2 pepperoni. I recommend asking for it well done because i like crispy crust, but that's your personal preference. If you want good old fashioned real deal pizza, this is one of the go to spots. It very well might be the best. Also remember they don't deliver. That should say it all. They have been around for over 45 years and they never did deliveries. If you want the best you have to go to them. And it well worth the trip. Go grab a few pies and thank me later when your going for your 4th or 5th slice lol.
